Investors calling for a 10-15% $TSLA decline today don’t get the diff between a 2% secondary and a 2% block sale by the CEO. The former is dilutive (reduces EPS by 2%) and weighs on the stock for days. The latter is just a block trade by GS/MS and gets done in a day. TSLA -2.8%.
